table-0981-964.caption: Design
data: Beauty Within Reach Tower It is the final hall of the entry sequence. It is a six bay and two level tower without portico. It was used as the women's meeting area. The name refers to the view of distant hill and suburbs from the top level. It has a front court planted with Cassia and a carved brick gate.

Gate A three bay structure with two bays enclosed as side rooms. It is gableless using instead horsehead walls and a bird motif decorated ridge. It faces a dragon wall across a semiprivate courtyard planted with Weeping Scholar Trees.

Grand Reception Hall The third hall in the sequence. Also called the Hall of Accumulated Benevolence, and Ten Thousand Volume Hall, it is a three bay. It was used for meeting guests. A carved brick gate at the front depicts scenes from two Kunqu operas; Guo Ziyi Presents Birthday Gifts, and Wen Wang visits the Talents. It is gableless using instead horsehead walls, and a ridge decorated with birds. The attached courtyard is planted with Jade Magnolia.

Sedan-Chair Hall The second hall in the entry sequence. A three bay hall with front portico. In is named for the sedan chair used to carry imperial officials. It is connected by a covered passage to the front gate, creating the illusion the two are one structure.
Barrier of Clouds Rockery A yellowstone rockery meant to resemble a bank of fog.

Duck Shooting Corridor A boat shaped three bay full gable pavilion with pillar couplest in front of the Meditation Study, also called the Prunus mume Pavilion. Shooting ducks was game played during the Ming Dynasty.

Inner Garden A 667m 2 courtyard connected to the main garden by the Fisherman's Retreat Gate. It was used as a women's area. It is built in the style of a Ming Dynasty courtyard decorated with rockerys and scholar stones.

Truth and Harmony Guest House A three-bay hall with portico on three sides and hipped gable roofline used as a guest house. It is named after a proverb, "To conduct yourself harmoniously and support the truth." The window screen have elaborately carved net motifs which allude to the garden's name.

Watching Pine and Appreciating Paintings Studio A three bay hall with full gables and ridge decorated with birds used as an art studio. The yard in front of this hall is planted with several pine and cypress trees from the Ming Dynasty. There is an annex attached to the side which connects with the Late Spring Cottage.
Leading to Quitetude Bridge A three step bridge, the smallest in Suzhou.

Dr. Wagner defeated El Halcon in a tournament final to win the vacant title.
The exact date on which Tarzan Boy vacated the title is unknown, which means the title reign lasted between 1031 and 1069 days.
Vampiro defeated Tarzan Boy in a decision match for the vacant title.
